---

1 olive oil
20 g butter
¼ tsp salt
1 packet flaked almonds
1 carrot
1 bag green beans
½ head broccoli
1 tbs balsamic vinegar
1 tbs brown sugar
1 tbs water
1 packet chicken thigh
2 Kumara
1 clove garlic
1 packet Cherry Sauce

Bring a medium saucepan of lightly salted water
to the boil. Peel the kumara and cut into large
chunks. Cook the kumara in the boiling water until
easily pierced with a fork, 10-15 minutes. Drain
and return the kumara to the saucepan. Add the
butter and the salt, then mash until smooth. Cover
to keep warm.

While the kumara is cooking, heat a large frying
pan over a medium-high heat. Toast the flaked
almonds, tossing, until golden, 2-3 minutes.
Transfer to a small bowl. Thinly slice the carrot
into sticks. Trim the green beans. Finely chop the
garlic. Cut the broccoli (see ingredients) into small
florets and roughly chop the stalk.

Return the frying pan to a medium-high heat with
a drizzle of olive oil. Cook the carrot, green beans
and broccoli with a dash of water, tossing, until
softened, 4-6 minutes. Add the garlic, then season
with salt and pepper and cook until fragrant,
1-2 minutes. Transfer the veggies to a bowl and
cover to keep warm.

Season both sides of the chicken thigh. Wipe
out the frying pan, then return to a medium-high
heat with a drizzle of olive oil. Cook the chicken,
turning occasionally, until browned and cooked
through, 10-14 minutes.

TIP: The chicken is cooked through when it's no
longer pink inside.

While the chicken is cooking, combine the cherry
sauce, balsamic vinegar, brown sugar and the
water in a small bowl, then season. When the
chicken is cooked, remove the pan from the heat,
then add the cherry-balsamic glaze. Turn the
chicken to coat.

TIP: Stand back! The glaze can spit when added to
the hot pan.

Slice the glazed chicken. Divide the kumara mash,
garlic veggies and chicken between plates. Spoon
over any remaining glaze. Sprinkle with the toasted
almonds to serve.